roll slow motion because we knew it was sure, as we hadbeen sure, of its strapping pace, and now that restraint, thatstateliness...

Suddenly there came from somewhere within the natural jumble of oursurroundings a roar of unearthly ecstasy.

"Goodness," said Iris, "I do hope that's not a happy escapee fromKanner's Circus." (No relation--at least, so it seemed--to the pianist.)

We walked on, now side by side: after the first of the half-dozen timesit crossed the looping main road, our path grew